This move definitely not the best. Computer analysis views this move as a mistake and that Qxf3 was the best. Very true, for this move has a 2-in-1 damage. First, the pawn structure for white is thrown off now. It's a 2-in-1 damage because with the pawn structure the way it is now, if white castles king-side, his king is wide open and vulnerable to attack, so this move is definitely a mistake.

I retreat the knight, but this is viewed by the computer analysis as an inaccuracy. It says O-O was best? I question that. As I said in the previous comment, it would leave the king open for an attack. True it can be defended, but in my view, it is not the best move right now, but that's my view.
